First, you should know what you want to have as result of logging. It does not matter recursive you code or not if you log something then you will have it in you logs.

So, if you really have to log event inside the cycle then I guess, may be you want to split significant events and not. 

For example (use slf4j and logback):
Log events normal way.
```
    LOGGER.trace(&quot;log message&quot;);
```
Log significant things with info level and upper and all other things with trace then add two appenders with different log levels.
logback.xml:
```
    &lt;appender name=&quot;FILE&quot; class=&quot;ch.qos.logback.core.rolling.RollingFileAppender&quot;&gt;
        &lt;file&gt;@project.artifactId@.log&lt;/file&gt;
        &lt;append&gt;true&lt;/append&gt;
        &lt;filter class=&quot;ch.qos.logback.classic.filter.ThresholdFilter&quot;&gt;
            &lt;level&gt;INFO&lt;/level&gt;
        &lt;/filter&gt;
        &lt;encoder&gt;
            &lt;charset&gt;UTF-8&lt;/charset&gt;
            &lt;pattern&gt;%-8level %-25d{YYYY-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.SSS} %logger - %msg%n&lt;/pattern&gt;
        &lt;/encoder&gt;
    &lt;/appender&gt;

   &lt;appender name=&quot;FILE_TRACE&quot; class=&quot;ch.qos.logback.core.rolling.RollingFileAppender&quot;&gt;
        &lt;file&gt;@project.artifactId@_trace.log&lt;/file&gt;
        &lt;append&gt;true&lt;/append&gt;
        &lt;encoder&gt;
            &lt;charset&gt;UTF-8&lt;/charset&gt;
            &lt;pattern&gt;%-8level %-25d{YYYY-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.SSS} %logger - %msg%n&lt;/pattern&gt;
        &lt;/encoder&gt;
    &lt;/appender&gt;

    &lt;root level=&quot;ERROR&quot;&gt;
        &lt;appender-ref ref=&quot;FILE&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;appender-ref ref=&quot;FILE_TRACE&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;/root&gt;
```
In this case one log file will have everything and the second one only significant data (errors, warnings and info). 

So, it will be easier to monitoring significant things using file with INFO level and you will have full log in file with TRACE level.

